  "title": "Shipping Officer [Sea/Air Freight] - Import/Export | Changi - Up to $3.5k [0580]",
  "description": "<ul><li>Mon - Friday 8:30am to 5:30pm Saturday 8:30am to 12:30 pm </li><li>Working Location: Changi South</li><li>Salary : $2500 - $3500</li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities </strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate and manage the logistics and shipping operations for both inbound and outbound freight, ensuring timely and efficient delivery</li><li>Assist in preparing and reviewing shipping documents, including airway bills, bills of lading, and other required import/export paperwork</li><li>Monitor and track shipments to ensure smooth transportation from origin to destination, updating clients and stakeholders as needed</li><li>Inspect cargo in the warehouse, ensuring proper storage, handling, and compliance with safety regulations</li><li>Perform data entry tasks related to shipment tracking, cargo details, and other logistics documentation</li><li>Support permit declarations and ensure compliance with customs regulations</li><li>Collaborate with freight forwarders, carriers, and internal teams to resolve any operational issues or delays</li><li>Provide support to both clients and internal teams, answering queries related to shipments, documentation, and logistics processes</li><li>Carry out any ad-hoc duties as required to support the logistics department and meet operational goals</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>With relevant working experience</li></ul><p><br />The Supreme HR Advisory Pte. Ltd || 14C7279</p><p>Chua Jie Ying (Cai Jie Ying), Evelynn || EA Personnel License R24120580</p>",
